![](https://media.newscentermaine.com/assets/NCM/images/f8434a2c-790e-4107-95e9-edaa2fd7dc8c/20251223T193148/f8434a2c-790e-4107-95e9-edaa2fd7dc8c_16x9.jpg) ![](https://media.newscentermaine.com/assets/NCM/images/f8434a2c-790e-4107-95e9-edaa2fd7dc8c/20251223T193148/f8434a2c-790e-4107-95e9-edaa2fd7dc8c_1140x641.jpg)

Credit: NCM

"This storm is anticipated to create slick travel on Christmas Eve," Mills said in a statement. "If you’re traveling on Tuesday or Wednesday, please take necessary precautions to arrive safely at your holiday destination. Give plenty of room to plowing crews and first responders working to keep people safe. I wish Maine people a safe and Merry Christmas."

The closure applies to all state offices statewide. [The Maine Emergency Management Agency](https://www.maine.gov/mema/home) said it is coordinating with the [Department of Transportation,](https://www.maine.gov/dot/) Maine’s electric utilities, and local emergency management partners as the storm approaches.

Travelers are urged to monitor road conditions and plan for potential delays.

